# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables for the Halyard Table LiveKit SFU.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and populate
# with real values before bringing the SFU up.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Publicly-reachable address of Atlas. For the Halyard Table,
# this is the DNS name that halyard.atlas-sjsu.duckdns.org
# ultimately resolves to. LiveKit advertises this in ICE
# candidates so remote browsers can reach the media ports.
#
# For Tailscale-only deployments (e.g., Keeper-and-players
# all on Tailscale), use the Atlas Tailscale IP 100.68.134.21.
# For public duckdns, use the resolved A-record IP.
LIVEKIT_EXTERNAL_IP=

# TURN shared secret. 32+ bytes of cryptographic randomness.
# Generate with:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
# Must match what the Halyard-keeper-backend embeds in the TURN
# credentials it mints for browsers.
LIVEKIT_TURN_SECRET=

# Optional — Redis for horizontal scaling. Leave blank for
# single-instance deployments (default).
# LIVEKIT_REDIS_HOST=localhost:6379
